title: iPhone 6s and iPhone 6s Plus: What Apple changed
text:
Tags: Apple , Hey Siri , iPhone , iPhone 6 , iPhone 6 Plus , iPhone 6S , iPhone 6s Plus 
At its September 2015 event in Cupertino today, Apple announced the iPhone 6s and iPhone 6s Plus , succeeding the iPhone 6 and iPhone 6 Plus respectively. Apple’s ninth-generation phones are now official. 
Pre-orders begin September 12, and the devices will begin shipping September 25. Before you get your credit card ready, and assuming you’re not enthused by what’s coming in Android 6.0 Marshmallow or in Windows 10 Mobile, you might want to see what exactly you’re getting. The comparison tables below show you exactly what Apple has changed, comparing the iPhone 6 and the iPhone 6s as well as the iPhone 6 Plus and the iPhone 6s Plus. iPhone 6
